"distribute_over_tranches" is a program by R. Dodier whose aim is to
parallelize the execution of maxima by sending computations to several
Unix processes, and collecting the results in the main program. As such it
uses interprocess communication and requires a maxima compiled with sbcl.
It can be found in R. Dodier folder of maxima-packages.

The present version "distribute_over_tranches_mt.lisp" is a modification of
the original one making more use of specific sbcl features to simplify
the interprocess communication, and with the addition of handlers for
several possible error situations.

Finally "distribute_over_tranches_thread.lisp" is another way to
achieve the same parallelism, using threads in just one Unix
process. Here we use the sbcl threading support.

Both versions run the examples in R. Dodier folder with the same
result as his one. These examples show that it is possible to run long
maxima computations by distributing them in several processes or
threads. Of course a much more extensive example set would be
necessary.

Ref. https://github.com/robert-dodier/maxima-packages/tree/master/robert-dodier/distribute_over_tranches.
The sbcl documentation, including looking at the source code.
